This directory contains the 0.6.0 release of Timeline.

Timeline is a cross-platform application for displaying and navigating events
on a timeline. 

Timeline is free software, distributed under the GNU General Public License,
version 3. For more information, see the file COPYING.

Icons are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0
Unported License. For more information, see file icons/COPYING.

Translations are licensed under the modern, simplified BSD license and are
managed on Launchpad: http://translations.launchpad.net/thetimelineproj.

Overview of the files in this directory:

devdoc/         - Documentation for developers to understand the code
help_resources/ - Images used by the help system
icons/          - Images used for application icon
po/             - Translation files (imported from Launchpad)
src/            - Python source code (run with 'python main.py')
tests/          - Unit tests (run with 'python run.py')
AUTHORS         - Lists all people that have contributed to the project
CHANGES         - Lists changes between releases (releases notes)
COPYING         - A copy of the GNU General Public License, version 3
INSTALL         - Instructions how to install Timeline
release.py      - Script to generate a source package
SConstruct      - File read by SCons to build parts of the application

The project's website is intended as the first source of information about the
project. It includes information about how to download the software, how to get
help, and how to participate:

  http://thetimelineproj.sourceforge.net/

All development takes place here:

  http://sourceforge.net/apps/trac/thetimelineproj/
